# ACS — Provider API Keys
# ============================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your key.
# NEVER commit .env to git — it is already in .gitignore.
#
# ACS auto-detects your provider in this priority order:
#   1. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  → uses Anthropic (default, highest quality)
#   2. OPENAI_API_KEY     → uses OpenAI
#   3. GEMINI_API_KEY     → uses Gemini
#   4. No key found       → falls back to Ollama (local, no key needed)
#
# Uncomment ONE block below, or pass --provider explicitly:
#   python .acs/scripts/acs_ingest.py --input plan.md --provider openai
# ============================================================

# --- Anthropic (default) ---
# Best quality. Get key: https://console.anthropic.com
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# --- OpenAI ---
# Get key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here

# --- Google Gemini ---
# Free tier available. Get key: https://aistudio.google.com
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-key-here

# --- Ollama (local — no key needed) ---
# Install: https://ollama.com/download
# Then run: ollama pull llama3 && ollama serve
# Then use: python .acs/scripts/acs_ingest.py --provider ollama --model llama3

# ============================================================
# Project-specific environment variables (add below as needed)
# ============================================================
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/dbname
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
